cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper describes a novel storyboarding scheme for a mobile robot user. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper uses a pre-trained convolutional neural network to extract image features. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the proposed approach incorporates user interest in the storyboarding process. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses a Gaussian process smoothing algorithm to reduce the number of image comparisons required. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper discusses the generation of user-specific saliency or attention maps.
